{
  "texts": [
    "(1) The bigger model does not mean that the quality is better.",
    "This premise proved to be false, evidently because researchers need vast amounts of data to train very large models and very often such data is not clear enough.",
    "On the contrary, when we clean the data very well for fine-tuning, we can bring the model quality much higher in specific domains, e.g. clinical text.",
    "We reached the point when the data quality was more important than the model's size.",
    "One key takeaway for researchers and practitioners from this point is that if it is possible to get 250,000 clean segments in a new low-resource language, it is capable of fine-tuning large language models (LLMs) and get a good enough engine in this language."
  ]
}